'''Debora T. Cahn''' is an American television writer, most notable for her work on ''[[The West Wing (TV series)|The West Wing]]''. Following ''The West Wing''{{'}}s end, Cahn was hired as a producer for ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/newswire.aspx?id=7154 |title=Development Update: May 9-12 |publisher=The Futon Critic |date=May 12, 2006 |accessdate=October 28, 2013}}</ref>
==Biography== Cahn was raised in a [[American Jews|Jewish]] family.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Bloom|first=Nate|authorlink= |title=The big Emmys, and the other Emmys |publisher=[[J. The Jewish News of Northern California]]|date= September 4, 2018|url=https://www.jweekly.com/2018/09/04/the-big-emmys-and-the-other-emmys/ |accessdate=}}</ref> She graduated from Barnard College and received a master's degree in acting from the American Repertory Theater's Institute for Advanced Theater Training at Harvard.<ref name=NYTWedding>{{Cite web|last= |first= |authorlink= |title= Deborah Cahn, Michael Heller |publisher=[[New York Times]]|date= July 2, 2006|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/07/02/fashion/weddings/02cahn.html |accessdate=}}</ref> In 2006, Cahn married Michael Heller.<ref name=NYTWedding />
== Awards and nominations == In 2005, Cahn won the [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: Episodic Drama]] for the fifth season episode "The Supremes".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wga.org/wga-awards/previous-nominees-winners2.aspx |title=Previous Nominees & Winners |publisher=Writers Guild of America |accessdate=October 28, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6XjARCjVO?url=http://www.wga.org/wga-awards/previous-nominees-winners2.aspx |archivedate=April 12, 2015 |df= }}</ref> In 2006 and 2007, Cahn was part of the writing staff for two television series' nominated for the [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Drama Series]] and the [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: Dramatic Series]]; ''The West Wing'' in 2006 and ''Grey's Anatomy'' in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.emmys.com/shows/west-wing |title=The West Wing |publisher=Academy of Television Arts & Sciences |accessdate=October 28, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wga.org/subpage_newsevents.aspx?id=1493 |title=2006 Writers Guild Awards Television and Radio Nominees Announced |publisher=Writers Guild of America |date=December 14, 2005 |accessdate=October 28, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.emmys.com/shows/greys-anatomy |title=Grey's Anatomy |publisher=Academy of Television Arts & Sciences |accessdate=October 28, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite press |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2006/12/13/2007-writers-guild-awards-television-and-radio-nominees-announced-23095/20061213wga01/ |title=2007 Writers Guild Awards Television & Radio Nominees Announced |publisher=Writers Guild of America |date=December 13, 2006 |accessdate=October 28, 2013}}</ref>
