[[File:Otto BEYER "In der Mittagshitze".png|thumbnail|[[Otto Beyer]]: ''In der Mittagshitze'', 1919]] The '''Free Secession''' ({{lang-de|Freie Secession}}) was an association of [[modern art]]ists in [[Berlin]] organizing joint exhibitions 1914–1923.<ref name="Schubert 2010"/>
The Free Secession was formed after 42 members in late 1913 left the [[Berlin Secession]], which thereby lost a majority of its members and nearly all of its most prominent artists.<ref name="DB ML"/><ref name="KK 2013"/> [[Max Liebermann]], a former co-founder and leader of the Berlin Secession was made honorary president of the Free Secession.
